Provincial leaders in the Gauteng are being sworn-in on Thursday at Emoyeni Conference Centre. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng's new MECs are being sworn-in on Thursday at Emoyeni Conference Centre. Premier David Makhura announced his Cabinet on Wednesday, which brought a mixed reaction. There are six new faces in Gauteng’s executive council. Makhura’s deputy in the ANC, Panyaza Lesufi has been moved from Education to Finance and e-Government portfolio. The rest of Makhura’s cabinet comprises of the following;